.TH TMPLR 1 "__DATE__" "__VERSION__" "tmplr tool"
.SH NAME
tmplr \- Template processing utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tmplr
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tmplr
is a command-line utility for processing templates with variable substitution and filtering.
.PP
The utility reads template files and substitutes variables with values, producing the processed output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BR -V ", " --version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.BR -l ", " --list
List all available variables in the template.
.TP
.BR -o ", " --output " FILE"
Write output to FILE instead of stdout.
.TP
.BR -v ", " --verbose
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.BR -D " KEY=VALUE"
Set a variable override.
.TP
.BR -F " KEY=VALUE"
Set a variable filter.
.TP
.BR -L " LIMIT"
Set maximum block lines.
.TP
.BR -S " SEPARATOR"
Set item separator.
.TP
.BR -I " SEPARATOR"
Set iteration separator.
.TP
.BR -p " PREFIX"
Set variable prefix.
.TP
.BR -m " MAXLEN"
Set maximum value length.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B tmplr template.txt
Process template.txt and output to stdout.
.TP
.B tmplr -D name=World template.txt
Process template.txt with name=World override.
.TP
.B tmplr -F name=World template.txt
Process template.txt with name=World filter.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/tmplr.conf
Global configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.tmplrrc
User-specific configuration file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tmplr (3),
.BR tmplr_macros (3)
